            <div type="translation" resp="part:emfr">
                <p n="1">
                    Prosperity! Fortune! 
                </p>
                
                <p n="3">                    
                    <gap reason="lost"/> <supplied reason="lost">year of the king Rājendra Cōḻa <hi rend="italic">alias</hi></supplied> the king Pa<supplied reason="lost">rakesarivarman</supplied>, 
                </p>
                
                <p n="1-3">                    
                    who took <gap reason="ellipsis"/><note><foreign>meykkīrtti</foreign> of Rājendra I Cōḻa.</note>
                </p>
                
                <p n="4">
                    <supplied reason="subaudible">There are</supplied>, for the Mahādeva of Tirumutukuṉṟam in Koṭumpāḷūr, six goats that the bard of this village, Arumoḻitēva Cakkai <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Viḻuppēraiyaṉ Vikkiramakēcari gave <gap reason="lost"/>
                </p>
                
                <p n="4-5">
                    The gold accrued from these seven goats is one <foreign>kaḻañcu</foreign>.  
                </p>
                
